sequenceDiagram
    participant OVMS as OVMS gRPC/REST Handler<br/>(consuming application)
    participant Runtime as OpenVINO Runtime<br/>ov::Core
    participant Frontend as Model Frontend<br/>(ONNX/TF/IR/PyTorch/Paddle/TFLite)
    participant FS as File System<br/>(model storage)
    participant Graph as Core Graph Layer<br/>ov::Model
    participant Transforms as Transformation Pipeline<br/>Common + LPT + Snippets
    participant Plugin as Device Plugin<br/>(CPU/GPU/Auto/Hetero)
    participant HW as Hardware<br/>Intel CPU (oneDNN/AMX)<br/>Intel GPU (OpenCL)

    Note over OVMS,HW: Flow 1: Model Loading (compile_model)

    OVMS->>Runtime: ov::Core::compile_model(model_path, device)<br/>C++ API (in-process)
    Runtime->>Frontend: Select frontend by format<br/>(file extension / magic bytes)
    Frontend->>FS: Read model file<br/>(File I/O)
    FS-->>Frontend: Model data<br/>(protobuf / flatbuffers / XML+bin)
    Frontend->>Graph: Convert to ov::Model<br/>(unified IR graph, 200+ ops)
    Graph-->>Runtime: ov::Model (in-memory graph)

    Runtime->>Transforms: Apply graph optimizations
    Note over Transforms: Constant folding<br/>Precision conversion<br/>Op fusion
    Transforms->>Transforms: Low Precision Transforms<br/>(INT8/INT4 quantization)
    Transforms->>Transforms: Snippets<br/>(kernel code generation)
    Transforms-->>Runtime: Optimized ov::Model

    Runtime->>Plugin: plugin->compile_model()<br/>Plugin API (in-process)
    Note over Plugin: Generate device-specific<br/>executable network
    Plugin-->>Runtime: CompiledModel

    Note over OVMS,HW: Flow 2: Inference Execution

    OVMS->>Runtime: compiled_model->create_infer_request()<br/>C++ API (in-process)
    Runtime-->>OVMS: InferRequest handle

    OVMS->>Runtime: infer_request->set_input_tensor(data)<br/>C++ API (in-process)
    OVMS->>Runtime: infer_request->infer()<br/>C++ API (in-process)
    Runtime->>Plugin: Execute inference<br/>Plugin API (in-process)
    Plugin->>HW: Execute compute kernels<br/>oneDNN/OpenCL/xbyak JIT
    HW-->>Plugin: Compute results
    Plugin-->>Runtime: Output tensors
    Runtime-->>OVMS: infer_request->get_output_tensor()<br/>Inference result

    Note over OVMS,HW: All communication is in-process (C++ API calls)<br/>No network traffic, no encryption, no auth
